title: The (P,D) Reaction At 65 Mev

x4freetext: THE (P,D) REACTION AT 65 MEV

x4codes.hlp: University of Maryland, College Park, MD, United States of America

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.255, p.187 (1975)

x4codes.hlp: University of Maryland, College Park, MD, United States of America

x4freetext: 1 MM SI FOR DE, 4 MM SI(LI) FOR E
THE ENERGY RESOLUTION OF DETECTOR SYSTEM TO THE
INCIDENT BEAM WAS ABOUT 70 KEV.  THE OVERALL
ENERGY RESOLUTION WAS BETWEEN 150 KEV AND 300 KEV
(FWHM) DEPENDING ON THE ANGLE AND TARGET.
POLYSTYRENE OF 1.06 MG PER SQUARE CM WAS USED
FOR THE TARGET.  ISOTOPIC ABUNDANCE OF C-12 WAS 91
PERCENT.
